xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2382</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-iii-6.2.5</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-6.2.5.xml</fr:route><fr:authors /><fr:number>6.2.5</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-6.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4"
href="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="6.2.4" /> allows us to construct, by induction, proper hypercovers of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(0) &quot;">
      We take <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_0\colon  X_0\to  S]]></fr:tex>, proper and surjective.
      Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{X_0\}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>-truncated proper hypercover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> (<fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.8"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.8.xml"
number="5.3.8" />), and it is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split.
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(1) &quot;">
      We take <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1\colon  N_1\to \operatorname {cosq}(\{X_0\})_1]]></fr:tex>, i.e. <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1\colon  N_1\to  X_0\times _S X_0]]></fr:tex>.
      Applying <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4"
href="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="6.2.4" />, we associate to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1]]></fr:tex> the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>-truncated augmented simplicial topological space
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         {}_1X_\bullet          = \left (         N_1{\textstyle \coprod } X_0         \xleftarrow [\to ]{\to } X_0         \to  S         \right ).       ]]></fr:tex>
      Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1]]></fr:tex> to be chosen such that
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         f'_1         \colon  N_1{\textstyle \coprod } X_0\to  X_0\times _S X_0       ]]></fr:tex>
      is proper and surjective (for example, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1]]></fr:tex> is proper and surjective).
      Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_1X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>-truncated proper hypercover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(k+1) &quot;">
      Assume that we have already constructed an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>-truncated proper hypercover <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_kX_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex>.
      We take <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{k+1}\colon  N_{k+1}\to (\operatorname {cosq}({}_kX_\bullet ))_{k+1}]]></fr:tex> and, applying <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4"
href="hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="6.2.4" />, we associate to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{k+1}]]></fr:tex> an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(k+1)]]></fr:tex>-truncated augmented semi-simplicial space <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{k+1}X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>.
      Suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{k+1}]]></fr:tex> is such that
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         f'_{k+1}         \colon  {}_{k+1}X_{k+1}         \to  \operatorname {cosq}({}_kX_\bullet )_{k+1}       ]]></fr:tex>
      is proper and surjective (for example, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{k+1}]]></fr:tex> is proper and surjective).
      Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{k+1}X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(k+1)]]></fr:tex>-truncated proper hypercover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(âˆž) &quot;">
      The <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_kX_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> thus constructed are the successive skeletons of an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>-split proper hypercover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

  </html:ol>
